{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PKPCJ7bgtuzBqKNzwqnPkg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 008 User Profile — Transaction History\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P1 |\n     9→| Phase | 3 |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 9 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→First iteration of player profiles. Players can view a chronological list of\n    17→their own game transactions — joins, wins, losses, and refunds — across all\n    18→games (Coinflip, Lord of the RNGs, Close Call). Data is stored in a new\n    19→backend ledger table and served via an authenticated API endpoint. The\n    20→existing mock-driven `ProfileTransactions` frontend component is wired to the\n    21→real data.\n    22→\n    23→No on-chain footprint. No aggregate stats, XP, levels, or social features in\n    24→this iteration.\n    25→\n    26→## User Stories\n    27→\n    28→- As a player, I want to see every game transaction tied to my wallet so I can\n    29→  track what I wagered, won, or lost.\n    30→- As a player, I want the list to update automatically after a game settles so\n    31→  I don't have to refresh.\n    32→\n    33→---\n    34→\n    35→## Scope Alignment\n    36→\n    37→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Phase 3 — \"Basic player profile/history from\n    38→  indexed data\"; Launch checklist — \"Basic profile/history available and\n    39→  accurate\"\n    40→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    41→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 3\n    42→\n    43→## Required Context Files\n    44→\n    45→- `services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client & query functions\n    46→- `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — settlement write path (coinflip + lord)\n    47→- `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` — closecall settlement write path (settleRound function)\n    48→- `services/backend/src/routes/` — existing route patterns\n    49→- `services/backend/migrations/` — migration files (see Developer Reference below)\n    50→- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` — mock profile system + components\n    51→\n    52→## Contract Files\n    53→\n    54→- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/types.ts` — `ProfileTransaction` type (frontend shape)\n    55→- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileTransactions.tsx` — table component to wire\n    56→\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→## Functional Requirements\n    60→\n    61→### FR-1: `user_transactions` Ledger Table\n    62→\n    63→A new PostgreSQL table that stores one row per user-visible game event.\n    64→\n    65→**Schema:**\n    66→\n    67→| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n    68→|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n    69→| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | PK | Auto-increment |\n    70→| `wallet` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Player wallet address |\n    71→| `game` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall` |\n    72→| `match_id` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Links to rounds/closecall_rounds |\n    73→| `event` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `join`, `win`, `loss`, `refund` |\n    74→| `amount_lamports` | `BIGINT` | NOT NULL | Wager (join) or payout (win) or refund amount |\n    75→| `tx_sig` | `TEXT` | | On-chain transaction signature (nullable until confirmed) |\n    76→| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | NOT NULL DEFAULT now() | Event timestamp |\n    77→\n    78→**Indexes:**\n    79→- `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` on `(wallet, created_at DESC)` — paginated history\n    80→- `idx_user_tx_match_id` on `(match_id)` — dedup / lookup\n    81→\n    82→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    83→- [ ] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` creates the table and indexes\n    84→- [ ] Migration runs cleanly on a fresh DB and on an existing DB\n    85→- [ ] No backfill of historical data (table starts empty)\n    86→\n    87→### FR-2: Write Path — Populate on Settlement\n    88→\n    89→The settlement worker writes to `user_transactions` when a round settles.\n    90→All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for\n    91→idempotency.\n    92→\n    93→**Coinflip** (commit-reveal, 1v1):\n    94→- **Join — creator**: Written when the create route inserts the round into DB\n    95→  (creator wallet is known at create time).\n    96→- **Join — opponent**: Written when PDA watcher detects phase change to LOCKED\n    97→  (opponent wallet readable from on-chain account).\n    98→- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert two rows.\n    99→  `win.amount_lamports` = payout (after fees). `loss.amount_lamports` =\n   100→  original wager.\n   101→\n   102→**Lord of the RNGs** (commit-reveal, multi-player):\n   103→- **No join rows** — the PDA watcher sees the round state change but not\n   104→  individual entries. Join visibility is deferred.\n   105→- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert one `win`\n   106→  row for the winner and one `loss` row per losing entry. Entries array is\n   107→  available from on-chain round data at settlement time.\n   108→\n   109→**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n   110→- **All rows at settlement**: When `settleRound()` in `closecall-clock.ts`\n   111→  completes, write one `join` + one outcome (`win`/`loss`/`refund`) row per\n   112→  entry. Entries are in the round's `green_entries`/`red_entries` JSONB.\n   113→- **Refund rows**: Only Close Call has backend-processed refunds (one-sided\n   114→  rounds, single player, equal price). Coinflip/Lord refunds are\n   115→  permissionless on-chain timeout — the backend doesn't process them.\n   116→\n   117→**Game name mapping**: DB stores `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`. API maps to\n   118→frontend `GameId`: `lord` → `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` → `close-call`.\n   119→\n   120→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   121→- [ ] Coinflip: creator join row written at create time\n   122→- [ ] Coinflip: opponent join row written at PDA watcher lock detection\n   123→- [ ] Coinflip: win + loss rows written at settlement with correct amounts and tx_sig\n   124→- [ ] Lord: win row for winner + loss rows for all losers at settlement\n   125→- [ ] Close Call: join + outcome rows per entry at settlement\n   126→- [ ] Close Call: refund rows written for refund outcomes\n   127→- [ ] `match_id` links back to the correct round in `rounds` or `closecall_rounds`\n   128→- [ ] No duplicate rows for the same event (idempotent via ON CONFLICT)\n   129→\n   130→### FR-3: API Endpoint — Transaction History\n   131→\n   132→```\n   133→GET /profile/transactions?cursor=<id>&limit=<n>&game=<filter>\n   134→```\n   135→\n   136→- **Auth**: JWT required. Returns transactions only for the authenticated\n   137→  wallet (from JWT `sub` claim). No wallet parameter in URL — prevents\n   138→  enumeration.\n   139→- **Pagination**: Cursor-based using `id` (descending). Default limit 20,\n   140→  max 50.\n   141→- **Filtering**: Optional `game` query param (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`).\n   142→- **Response shape**:\n   143→  ```json\n   144→  {\n   145→    \"transactions\": [\n   146→      {\n   147→        \"id\": 123,\n   148→        \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n   149→        \"matchId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f67890\",\n   150→        \"event\": \"win\",\n   151→        \"amountLamports\": \"5000000\",\n   152→        \"txSig\": \"5KtP...\",\n   153→        \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z\"\n   154→      }\n   155→    ],\n   156→    \"nextCursor\": \"122\"\n   157→  }\n   158→  ```\n   159→- `amountLamports` serialized as string (BigInt safety).\n   160→\n   161→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   162→- [ ] Endpoint requires valid JWT; returns 401 without one\n   163→- [ ] Returns only transactions for the authenticated wallet\n   164→- [ ] Cursor-based pagination works correctly (forward traversal)\n   165→- [ ] `game` filter restricts results to the specified game\n   166→- [ ] Default limit is 20; max clamped to 50\n   167→- [ ] Response matches the documented shape\n   168→- [ ] Empty result returns `{ \"transactions\": [], \"nextCursor\": null }`\n   169→\n   170→### FR-4: Frontend — Wire ProfileTransactions to Real Data\n   171→\n   172→Replace mock transaction data in the profile page with real API calls.\n   173→\n   174→- Fetch from `GET /profile/transactions` using the existing auth token.\n   175→- Infinite scroll or \"load more\" pagination using `nextCursor`.\n   176→- Show loading skeleton while fetching.\n   177→- Show empty state when no transactions exist.\n   178→- Each row links to the match deep-link page (`/coinflip/:matchId`,\n   179→  `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId`).\n   180→\n   181→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   182→- [ ] Profile transactions tab fetches from the real endpoint\n   183→- [ ] Pagination loads more results on scroll/click\n   184→- [ ] Loading and empty states render correctly\n   185→- [ ] Transaction rows link to the correct game match page\n   186→- [ ] Amounts display in SOL with USD estimate (via Pyth SOL/USD feed)\n   187→- [ ] Mock transaction generation is removed or bypassed when real data is available\n   188→\n   189→### FR-5: SOL/USD Price Display\n   190→\n   191→Transaction amounts are stored in lamports. The frontend displays them in SOL\n   192→with a USD estimate using the Pyth SOL/USD price feed (Hermes REST API —\n   193→already used for Close Call BTC/USD prices).\n   194→\n   195→- Backend exposes a cached `GET /price/sol-usd` endpoint (or piggybacks on an\n   196→  existing price infrastructure). Cache TTL ~60s.\n   197→- Frontend fetches the SOL/USD price and displays amounts as e.g.\n   198→  `0.50 SOL (~$75.00)`.\n   199→- If price is unavailable, show SOL amount only (no USD estimate). No error\n   200→  state — graceful degradation.\n   201→\n   202→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   203→- [ ] Backend serves cached SOL/USD price from Pyth Hermes\n   204→- [ ] Frontend displays lamport amounts as SOL with USD estimate\n   205→- [ ] Graceful fallback to SOL-only when price unavailable\n   206→\n   207→---\n   208→\n   209→## Success Criteria\n   210→\n   211→- A player who completes a game sees the transaction appear in their profile\n   212→  within seconds of settlement\n   213→- Transaction list is accurate — amounts, outcomes, and game types match\n   214→  on-chain reality\n   215→- Profile page loads transaction history performantly (< 500ms for first page)\n   216→\n   217→---\n   218→\n   219→## Dependencies\n   220→\n   221→- JWT auth system (spec 007 — already shipped)\n   222→- Settlement worker (coinflip + lord + closecall — already shipped)\n   223→- PDA watcher for join detection (already shipped)\n   224→\n   225→## Assumptions\n   226→\n   227→- No backfill of historical data — table starts empty, only new events recorded\n   228→- Close Call enforces one entry per player per round (on-chain constraint)\n   229→- No aggregate stats (win rate, total wagered, P&L) in this iteration\n   230→- No other players' transaction visibility — own wallet only\n   231→\n   232→---\n   233→\n   234→## Developer Reference\n   235→\n   236→> These notes exist so the implementor doesn't have to re-discover project\n   237→> conventions each time.\n   238→\n   239→### Database & Migrations\n   240→\n   241→| What | Where |\n   242→|------|-------|\n   243→| Migration files | `services/backend/migrations/NNN_snake_name.sql` |\n   244→| Migration runner | `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — auto-runs on server start (`pnpm start` = `migrate && server`) |\n   245→| DB client + query fns | `services/backend/src/db.ts` |\n   246→| DB config (schema) | `services/backend/src/db-config.ts` — supports `DB_SCHEMA` env var |\n   247→| Connection library | `postgres` (v3.4.0) — tagged template literal style |\n   248→\n   249→**Naming**: Files are `NNN_description.sql` where NNN is zero-padded sequential.\n   250→Next available: `007`.\n   251→\n   252→**Runner behavior**: Reads `migrations/` dir, parses version from filename\n   253→prefix, tracks applied versions in `_migrations` table, applies pending ones\n   254→inside `sql.begin()` transactions. Idempotent — safe to re-run.\n   255→\n   256→**Manual run**: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate` (uses `.env`).\n   257→**Check status**: `pnpm migrate:status`.\n   258→\n   259→### Settlement Write Paths (where to add INSERTs)\n   260→\n   261→| Game | File | Function | Insert after |\n   262→|------|------|----------|-------------|\n   263→| Coinflip settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleMatch()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 286) |\n   264→| Lord settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleLordRound()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 466) |\n   265→| Close Call settle | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | After DB update (~line 443-487) |\n   266→| Coinflip creator join | `src/routes/create.ts` | POST `/fairness/coinflip/create` | After round INSERT |\n   267→| Coinflip opponent join | `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` | `handleCoinflipChange()` | After lock detection (~line 113) |\n   268→| Close Call join+outcome | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | Same as settle — all rows at settlement |\n   269→\n   270→### Existing Schema (for reference)\n   271→\n   272→| Table | PK | Purpose |\n   273→|-------|----|---------|\n   274→| `rounds` | `pda` | Commit-reveal rounds (coinflip + lord). Has `creator`, `winner`, `settle_tx`, `amount_lamports`, `match_id` |\n   275→| `closecall_rounds` | `round_id` | Pari-mutuel rounds. Entries in JSONB: `green_entries` / `red_entries` = `[{ player, amountLamports }]` |\n   276→| `operator_events` | `id` | Audit log. `event_type` + JSONB `payload` |\n   277→| `auth_challenges` | `nonce` | JWT challenge nonces |\n   278→| `refresh_tokens` | `id` | JWT refresh token families |\n   279→| `closecall_candles` | `minute_ts` | Cached Hermes BTC prices |\n   280→\n   281→---\n   282→\n   283→## Validation Plan\n   284→\n   285→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   286→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   287→| 1 | Migration creates table + indexes | Run `pnpm migrate` on fresh + existing DB | Migration status shows applied |\n   288→| 2 | Settlement writes correct rows | Settle a coinflip match on devnet, query table | Row with correct wallet, game, event, amount, tx_sig |\n   289→| 3 | API returns own transactions only | Call endpoint with two different JWTs | Each sees only their own rows |\n   290→| 4 | Pagination works | Insert > 20 rows, paginate | Second page returns remaining rows |\n   291→| 5 | Frontend displays real data | Play a game, check profile page | Transaction appears with correct details |\n   292→\n   293→---\n   294→\n   295→## Completion Signal\n   296→\n   297→### Implementation Checklist\n   298→\n   299→- [x] [engine] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` — create table with schema from FR-1 (id, wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig, created_at) + indexes `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` and `idx_user_tx_match_id` + UNIQUE constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for idempotency. Add `insertUserTransaction()` and `getUserTransactions(wallet, cursor?, limit?, game?)` query functions to `db.ts`. Verify migration runs cleanly: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate:status`. (done: iteration 1)\n   300→- [x] [engine] Coinflip write paths — (a) In `src/routes/create.ts`: after inserting round into DB, write a `join` row for the creator (wallet = creator, game = \"coinflip\", amount_lamports = wager). (b) In `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` `handleCoinflipChange()`: after lock detection (~line 113), read opponent from on-chain account, write a `join` row for the opponent. (c) In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 286), write one `win` row (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row (amount_lamports = original wager) with tx_sig. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 2)\n   301→- [x] [engine] Lord of the RNGs write paths — In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 466), write one `win` row for the winner (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row per losing entry (amount_lamports = that entry's amountLamports). Entries array is available from `roundData.entries`. Game = \"lord\". No join rows for Lord (deferred — PDA watcher doesn't see individual entries). All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 3)\n   302→- [x] [engine] Close Call write paths — In `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` `settleRound()`: after DB settle update (~line 487), iterate `green_entries` and `red_entries` arrays. For each entry write: (a) one `join` row (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports), (b) one outcome row — `win` (amount_lamports = computed payout) if entry is on winning side, `loss` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if losing side, or `refund` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if `isRefund`. Game = \"closecall\", match_id = round_id. Payout per winner = `(entryAmount / winningSidePool) * (totalPool - fee)`. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 4)\n   303→- [x] [engine] API route `GET /profile/transactions` — Add `src/routes/profile.ts`, register at `/profile/transactions`. Require JWT auth middleware (reuse existing). Extract wallet from `req.auth.sub`. Query params: `cursor` (id, optional), `limit` (default 20, max 50), `game` (optional filter — accept both DB names and frontend names: `lord`/`lord-of-rngs`, `closecall`/`close-call`). Call `db.getUserTransactions()`. Map response: `game` field mapped to frontend names (`lord` → `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` → `close-call`), `amountLamports` as string, `matchId` camelCase. Return `{ transactions: [...], nextCursor: string | null }`. (done: iteration 5)\n   304→- [x] [engine] SOL/USD price endpoint — Add `GET /price/sol-usd` to backend. Fetch from Pyth Hermes REST API (SOL/USD feed ID: `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d`). Cache in-memory with ~60s TTL. Response: `{ price: number, expo: number, updatedAt: string }`. No auth required (public endpoint). Reuse existing Hermes fetch patterns from `closecall-clock.ts`. (done: iteration 6)\n   305→- [x] [frontend] Wire `ProfileTransactions` to real API — Update `ProfileTransaction` type in `types.ts` to match API shape: add `event` field (`join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund`), rename `outcome` → `event`, keep `gameId` mapped from API `game`. Create `useTransactions(cursor?, game?)` hook that calls `GET /profile/transactions` with auth header. Replace `getTransactions()` mock import in `ProfileTransactions.tsx` with the hook. Implement \"Load more\" button using `nextCursor`. Add loading skeleton and empty state. Each row links to deep-link page: `/coinflip/:matchId`, `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId` based on game. Display `join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund` event types with appropriate styling. (done: iteration 7)\n   306→- [x] [frontend] SOL amount display with USD estimate — Fetch SOL/USD price from `GET /price/sol-usd` (create `useSolPrice()` hook, cache in React state, refresh every 60s). Convert lamports → SOL (`amount / 1e9`). Display as `\"0.50 SOL (~$75.00)\"`. If price unavailable, show SOL only (no error). Apply to all amount cells in `ProfileTransactions`. (done: iteration 8)\n   307→- [x] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs) (done: iteration 9)\n   308→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   309→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for profile transactions page. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot